{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"8cc7bb1a31aba918","type":"text","text":"## 2040-2120 \n\n2048-2060: China Establishes **permanent lunar industrial bases** (regolith shielding, ISRU, self sufficient power), and develops cyberwarfare platforms targeted at space infrastructure. It also expands lunar footholds and starts Venus projects.\n\n**2060-2080s:** First lunar foundries export propellant and metals to cis-Earth orbits, China leverages economic dependencies (contracts, launch services, insurance) and performs targeted cyber operations to disable rivals’ launch infrastructure, satellite constellations, and manufacturing control systems. Rather than kinetic war, it uses **denial, data corruption, ransomware of fab-lines, and supply-chain infiltration** to hobble competitors.\n\n**2110–2150:** With rivals weakened, China consolidates control of cislunar logistics, key orbital hubs, and essential ISRU supply lines. It then tries to enforce preferential access, export controls on space materials, and exclusive contracts. Programmatic pivot to **Venus aerostat R&D** (leveraging high-temp materials and closed-loop life support matured on the Moon). Climate breakdown + resource exhaustion cause states to collapse into weak confederations while the Elites flee to Venus aerostats and space habitats, ~60–70% of humanity stranded on Earth and become unemployed, Few industries except resource extraction for orbital markets. Earth now is seen as a “degenerate planet”.","x":-1220,"y":100,"width":800,"height":500},
		{"id":"14b4d6ffd8c713c4","type":"text","text":"## 2220–2380 — Early Swarm Build-\n\n- **2230–2300:** Cheap nuclear/fusion tugs; Mercury/NEO extraction begins.\n- **2290s:** First **self-replicating fab chains** (cautiously sandboxed) start building solar collectors.\n- **2350:** Swarm captures **~0.5%** of solar output (patchy shells, lots of logistics friction).\n- **2380:** Swarm reaches **~2–3%**; the Sun now has a clear **mid-IR excess** visible to advanced observers.","x":-320,"y":100,"width":560,"height":500},
		{"id":"58205d570c9d6574","type":"text","text":"## 2440 — **Detection → Decision → Dispatch**\n\n- **2440:** Nearest Custodian **sentinel** flags Sol’s IR anomaly (internal threshold crossed—call it ~5% equivalent).\n- **2441–2446:** **Policy review** and classification (5 years): “Uplift, audit, and quarantine risk.”\n- **2446:** Sentinel at ~0.5 ly activates and **launches entry-bots** at ~0.15c.\n- **2449–2450:** Entry-bots **arrive** in the outer system (3–4 years transit), brake, and begin harvesting Kuiper/Oort material.","x":320,"y":100,"width":520,"height":500},
		{"id":"27531e57c161eeb8","type":"text","text":"## 2450–2465 — **Foundries Online, Avatars Arrive**\n\n- **2452–2458:** Kuiper **Foundry Nodes** spin up; nanofabs output utilities, comms, and matter printers.\n- **2460–2465:** First Custodian **avatars** instantiate locally (cloned bodies from patterns); the **info-network** comes online.\n- **Immediate effect:** Standards, logistics, and safety tooling **explode human productivity**.\n- **Start of Earth Revival Project (Shangri-La 2):** Rapid deployment of alien remediation toolset to high-priority biosites: atmospheric scrubbers built by nanofabs, contaminant sequestration matrices, microbial rebuild of soils, engineered phytoremediators.","x":920,"y":100,"width":875,"height":500},
		{"id":"4fa3d899505b38cc","type":"text","text":"## 2470–2650 — **Swarm Hyper-Acceleration (with custodian assistance)**\n\n- **2470s:** Safe, scaled **von Neumann** industrial trees (closely audited) replicate across inner system; **Mercury disassembly** ramps.\n- 2485-2525: “Shangri-La 2” rollout, - **Stage A (2485–2500):** Establish Planetary Management Authority (PMA) — hybrid human/alien advisory body controlling remediation priorities, rationed habitat reconstruction, and migration quotas. Dyson Swarm passes **10%** coverage.\n- **Stage B (2490–2525):** Build and commission large, alien-assisted **orbital ferry corridors** (mass drivers + fusion tugs + solar-sail relays). These allow steady transport of tens of millions over decades rather than centuries.\n- **Stage C (2500-2525):** “Shangri-La zones” — carefully rehabilitated, biodiverse reserves — are opened as model regions. Limited return of selected populations to steward and experiment with restored ecosystems.\n- **2550:** **25–30%**; power is no longer the bottleneck—**throughput & governance** are, steady outward migration accelerates as foundries mass-produce habitats and life-support. The alien relay network reduces transit energy costs, enabling larger Ark-class solar-sail transports.\n- **2625:** **50%** coverage; thermal management and traffic control become the dominant engineering problems. a substantial fraction of populations (maybe 50–70% of the original pre-collapse urban middle/elite classes and many labor cohorts) live off-Earth in a mix of Dyson habitats, orbital rings, Venus aerostats, Saturn/Titan colonies, and exodus starships. **Earth becomes a smaller, managed Gaia Remnant**, with a remnant lumpen population plus ecological stewards.\n- **2650:** **~60–65%**; transition planning to a tighter, layered architecture begins.","x":1880,"y":100,"width":837,"height":660},
		{"id":"72d75a91e1890a50","type":"text","text":"## 2660–2740 — **From Swarm to Shell (Gen-2)**\n\n- **2660–2700:** Pilot **segmented shell** rings (dense multi-layer bands) tested; stellar flux modulation proven.\n- **2700–2740:** Systematically **retire swarm elements** into a continuous multi-layer **Dyson shell** design (still with perforations and control gaps).\n- **Human society:** Inner-system capitalism (orbitals), Venusian state capitalism, Belt syndicalism, and Neptunian communism all persist—but now on **post-scarcity energy**. Frictions become _coordination_ and _safety_, not power.\n","x":2800,"y":100,"width":616,"height":420},
		{"id":"861e8194187d1c5c","type":"text","text":"## 2740–2795 — **Shell Completion & Catastrophe Window**\n\n- **2740:** Shell **>70%** effective closure; solar weather control gets aggressive (starspot management, flux shaping).\n- **2775:** Shell **~85–90%**; marginal gains demand riskier **stellar-magnetics** interventions.\n- **2792–2795:** The critical push: **>90–95%** closure (your requirement). A control instability in flux-shaping + shell resonance induces a **runaway feedback**.","x":3520,"y":100,"width":707,"height":420},
		{"id":"460123b93268b3b9","type":"text","text":"## 2795 — **The Superflare Event**\n\n- A star-sized, engineered **superflare** erupts.\n    \n- **Immediate outcomes:**\n    \n    - Large shell sectors vaporized; debris storms scour inner orbits.\n    - Multi-AU electromagnetic disturbance—also a **galactic beacon**.\n    - Custodians initiate **emergency quarantine** and withdraw their network relays from Sol.\n- **Political outcomes:** Accusations, opportunism, and seizure of stranded alien tooling; the seeds of your “betrayal + exile” age sprout.","x":4320,"y":100,"width":720,"height":420},
		{"id":"2033c23d76d368f1","type":"text","text":"## 2800–3000 — **Aftermath & Fragmentation**\n\n- **Earth/orbitals:** residual alien-derived tech, but without network integration but politically fractured; energy rationing while rebuilding.\n- **Venus:** Survives via disciplined planning; doubles down on “Forge ethos.”\n- **Belt:** Swings between mutual aid and piracy; salvages scorched shell debris.\n- **Neptune:** Stable but austere; becomes a health and governance outlier.\n- **Extrasolar offshoots:** Some groups had already slipped away with Custodian best-practices; without the network, many **strand and regress**—your post-apocalyptic diaspora.","x":5100,"y":100,"width":776,"height":420},
		{"id":"356e45b4fb669e0d","x":-570,"y":-120,"width":1650,"height":60,"type":"text","text":"# <center> Timeline</center>"}
	],
